cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for estimating driver gaze zones, which is a common problem in the field of human-computer interaction (HCI) and intelligent vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for this task, which is a popular machine learning technique, and hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of driver gaze for handoff time determination in autonomous vehicles, which is related to robotics and control, and hence, it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses a naturalistic driving dataset and examines the generalization capabilities of the CNN models, which is related to human factors and psychology, and hence, it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
